<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Necro's VS (Assorted Spell Casters ;&gt;)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?DarkBlight">DarkBlight</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:52 p.m. 26/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Necro's VS (Assorted Spell Casters ;&gt;)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Necromancers seem to have been the subject of debate these days's on numerous boards throughout the EQ community (Mainly over the DoT subject). I've read a plethora of posts and articles concerning Wizards and Druids (In search of that dream like "rounded" PvP machine) but have come rather short concerning news about Necro's.

<P>The current advantages Necro's have at this point:(I've only had the opportunity to plod around the relatively low levels, so any greater knowledge about their overall combat potential at the more advanced stages of the class would be appreciated)
<P>HP/Damage Causing Spells- Their equivalent of the Heal)
<P>DoT Spells- Nasty cumulative damage over time spells with a variety of after affects such as "slowing" down the victim’s movement to some degree
<P>Pet's- Portable Tankers, useful for "tangling" up the attention of most spell casters and soaking up damage otherwise meant for you.
<P>----------------------------------------------------------------------
<P>Again, the above is common knowledge to anyone off the banana boat. What interests me is the question of how the above "ferments" overtime compared to the other classes. For example CC's comparison of Wizards VS Druids, at certain levels the Druids have certain advantages over the Wizards and vice versa. So taking away all the bells and whistles of this post here are my questions:
<P>1. How efficient is the Necro class at the latter levels
<P>2. What classes can they compete against, and what classes should they most likly avoid in battle
<P>3. How does the Necro class compare in contrast to their spell weilding brethren.
<P>Many thanks,
<BR>DarkBlight
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
